# Assets Loans And Receivables Credit Outstanding Amount

## identifier
de14845

## type
float

## definition
This is the amount owed by borrowers at the end of the reporting period. Credit outstanding is the original loan or lease amount, less any repayments, including any redraw facilities drawn. The balance should be reported gross of provisions.

## guidance
Do not net any deposit balances in offset accounts against the outstanding loan amount. Exclude finance that has been written off.

## syntax
### xbrl
- balance=debit
- name=Assets.LoansAndReceivables.CreditOutstanding.Amount
- classification=baf/bafpo/bafpo5.02.15
- period=instant
